text.section:
Except as otherwise provided in subsection (b) of this section, in a real estate transaction involving a single-family dwelling, a real estate broker, an associate real estate broker, a real estate salesperson, or a lawyer acting as a real estate broker may not require a buyer, as a condition of settlement, to employ a particular:
title insurance company;
settlement company;
escrow company;
mortgage lender, or financial institution as defined in the Financial Institutions Article; or
title lawyer.
